Show Info

After attending a glamour-heavy reception for a Madonna concert in
Moscow, the presenter seeks out an alternative to the cosmopolitan
lifestyle found in modern Russian cities. Heading for the countryside
south of Moscow, he visits Yasnaya Polyana, the family estate of Leo
Tolstoy, and investigates efforts made by one of the renowned authors
ancestors, Count Vladimir Tolstoy, to reconnect with rural ideals
